# gen76: proof trace as structured memory. When the KB answers a query,
# the proof chain is stored so "how do you know?" can cite real state.
# Ground query -> "how do you know?" reads from stored proof.
> rex is a dog
< Learned: dog(rex).
> is rex a dog?
< Yes.
> how do you know?
< Because dog(rex).
# Rule-derived knowledge -> "how do you know?" reads the chain.
> every dog is a mammal
< Learned rule: mammal(X) :- dog(X).
> is rex a mammal?
< Yes.
> how do you know?
< Because mammal(rex) because dog(rex).
# Self-model -> proof from reflective facts.
> who are you?
< I am parrot0.
> how do you know?
< Because i_am(parrot0) is a reflective fact in my knowledge base.
# No proof stored yet -> honest admission.
> how do you know?
< I haven't answered a knowledge-based question yet, so I don't have a proof to share.
# Entity description -> proof stored.
> rex is a mammal
< Learned: mammal(rex).
> what is rex?
< rex is a dog; rex is a mammal.
> why?
< Because rex is a dog; rex is a mammal.
